### Description
The **Compose documents (DC) **task allows to process input data using the Doxee Platform 2 Document Composition software service in order to produce documents.

### Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- Click on the **Project &gt; Resource **field and select the Document Composition resource to use.

> Note

For more information, see:

[Document Composition Program Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/document-composition-program-resource-reference) 

- [Document Composition Project Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/document-composition-project-resource-reference)

- *(optional) *In the **Attributes **section, you may add up to 10 custom attributes to be added to the generated output file:

**{{Account name}}**

- **{{Account alias}}**

- **{{Input filename}}**

- **{{Job name}}**

- **{{Job number}}**

- **{{Job scope}}**

- **{{Step name}}**

- **{{Step alias}}**

- **{{Task name}}**

- **{{Tenant name}}**

- **{{Tenant alias}}**

- **{{Tenant stage}}**

> Important

You may also specify a custom parameter to indicate the maximum amount of memory to be used by the Java component of the Compose Documents (DC) task. For example, to increase the available memory from the default value (2GB) to 4GB, enter this string as a custom attribute:

`internals://settings/embeddedRenderer/maxHeap=4908`The *maxHeap *value must be less than the quota assigned when deploying the Batch Workflow resource. For more information, see: [Batch Workflow Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/batch-workflow-resource-reference).

A good practice is to set *maxHeap *to 75% of the allocated quota.

> Note

Custom parameters configured during the **Create job **action in the Batch Jobs portal may also be used as custom attributes (see [Doxee Platform Batch Jobs - Managing Jobs](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-jobs)).

- In the **Flags **field, select the execution options:

**Relaxed**: Skip the notification of some errors (for example, the system will not check that the generated files are correct).

- In the **Input **section, fill in the required fields:

In the **Pattern **field, enter the name of the input file or a filename pattern (for example, **.xml*).

- In the **Images **field, select the method to retrieve external images. The available options are:

**Static ***(default)*

- **Dynamic**: From the task input, based on a pattern

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- **Shared**: From a shared volume, specifying the last part of the filesystem path (for example: */MyDCProject*)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

The shared volume's full path is */mnt/doxee/repository/document_composition_om/external_image*.

This path is set by default and cannot be modified.

- In the **Output **section, fill in the required fields:

Select the **Format **of the output file. The available options are:

**PDF**

- **AFP**

- **PCL**

- **PS**

- **TIFF**

- **XLSX**

- **CSV**

- **Web**

> Note

The Web format corresponds to the Doxee Platform 2 "Pvideo/Pweb" format.

- **Email**

- **FOP**

> Note

The FOP format corresponds to the Doxee Platform 2 "XML embedded IF" format.

- Select the **Layout **of the output file. The available options are:

**Duplex**

- **Simplex**

- **Mixplex**

- In the **Target **field, enter the name of the target to use (default value: "DEFAULT").

- In the **Serializer **field, enter the **Name **of the serializer to use to produce the documents, as configured in the document composition resource.

- In the **Profile **field, enter the name of the management profile to use.

> Warning

The available management profiles are those defined in the Doxee Platform 2 Document Composition project on which the task is based. For more information, see: [Document Composition User Manual](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Document%2BComposition%2BUser%2BManual) &gt; [Files and Metadata](/doxee-platform/docs/files-and-metadata-1).

- In the **Overprints **field, enter the overprint profiles configured in the document composition resource.

> Note

Here's an example of the generated output file:
